This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on comparing the performance and energy efficiency of ARM64 and x64 servers for Big Data workloads. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of Apache Hadoop, which is a popular distributed computing framework. 

The paper also touches upon topics related to computer architecture (cs.AR) as it discusses the differences between the ARM64 and x64 architectures and their impact on performance and energy efficiency. 

The use of energy efficiency metrics such as Energy Delay Product (EDP) suggests that this paper could also belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category. 

The study of Big Data workloads and the use of Apache Hadoop also suggests that this paper could belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. 

Finally, the discussion of energy efficiency and reducing operational costs suggests that this paper could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NE) sub-category.
